Got it! Since you donâ€™t have an FPGA yet, weâ€™ll focus on **writing and simulating Verilog code** first. Later, when you get an FPGA, we can optimize it based on the available hardware. Also, since your FPGA is not very powerful, weâ€™ll design a **lightweight AI model** that can run efficiently on limited resources.

